&lt;/div>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Persistent Memory&lt;/strong> - Unlike regular variables that reset every time your component renders, useRef values stick around.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Silent Updates&lt;/strong> - When you change a useState value, React re-renders your component. Change a useRef value, and nothing happens on screen.&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;strong>Direct DOM Access&lt;/strong> - useRef gives you a direct line to the actual DOM element, bypassing React&amp;rsquo;s usual update system.&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
